<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="1015" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1015">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">811.42700 SE/3–2647: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00">April 7,
                                1947—7 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>410. On Apr 7 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] Dept dispatched note to Chinese
                        Ambassador stating readiness open negotiations Washington for agreement to
                        implement Fulbright<note n="5" xml:id="d1015fn1">Senator J. William
                            Fulbright of Arkansas, author of educational exchange program
                            legislation in Congress.</note> program and enclosing draft agreement
                        for study prior negotiation. Depins 293 Mar 26 transmitted draft
                            agreement.<note n="6" xml:id="d1015fn2">Neither printed.</note> Dept
                        would welcome Embs comments before opening discussions with Chinese here.
                        Cabling program plans soonest.<note n="7" xml:id="d1015fn3">
                            <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Sent Nanking 410, repeated Shanghai 573.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>